Great clinic! The staffs Sheqa and Irah greeted me with a warm smile, efficiently handled my registration and ensured I was comfortable while waiting. They also patiently answered my questions about my appointment and medication. Their professionalism and friendliness made my visit stress-free. A great asset to the clinic!
I was abit skeptical to visit due to the reviews however I glad I came. The 2 staff are friendly and doctor Azri checked my daughter carefully as she is suspected of hfmd.

This place is daylight robbery. I asked the receptionist when I came in (on a public holiday) if the consultation fee was the usual $20, but she didn't give me a straight answer. I had a common cold, so I didn't require any medications, and the fee was an insane $54.50, just for a consultation to get a day of sick leave. This is appalling behavior from the counter staff, deliberately withholding the PH surcharge until after I'd finished the consultation. And this isn't my first such experience with this clinic either.
